The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Bengal on Sistema radar 
                                                                                                               Bengal on Sistema radar 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 21: Sistema Shyam Teleservices, which today announced the launch of its CDMA services in Calcutta, will spend about $150 million in the state over the next three years. The company will launch the service under the MTS brand.        
	The company plans to invest $5.5 billion to have a pan-India presence by the middle of 2010. It has already invested $80 million in the city.         
	Sistema is a joint venture company in which Russias Sistema has a 74 per cent stake and the rest is owned by homegrown Shyam Telecom.         
	We will cover the whole of Bengal by the end of June. Bihar and Jharkhand will be under our towers by July and we hope to enter the Delhi market by August. We aim to launch our services in Mumbai by the end of this year, president and CEO Vsevolod Rozanov said.         
	The company is in talks with tower companies and infrastructure firms for the pan-India rollout. It has rolled out services in Rajasthan, Tamil Nadu and Kerala.                                                                                                                                        
